Rating: 4
I am among those who consider brussels sprouts to be a vile but nutritionally necessary evil, with the emphasis on 'vile'. I made this with some trepidation; I stemmed and left the sprouts raw before chopping them to smithereens in the processor, but followed the recipe to the letter otherwise. I loved it! Husband loved it! Neighbor (who also loathes sprouts) loved it! Who'd have guessed?

Rating: 4
Huge hit! This was a favorite at Christmas last year. I baked the brussel sprouts with olive oil and kosher salt, and otherwise followed the recipe. This dish is better if you let it sit for a while before serving, even overnight. My friends ask for it every time I have a dinner party!

