This is a surprisingly good recipe. I was concerned that the vinaigrette was too bland, but when everything was assembled, it was a big hit at the potluck to which I brought it.

Rating: 3
As written, this recipe is not very appealing, but it is a great starting point. I do not like boiled brussels sprouts, so I roasted them instead. Tossed them with olive oil, 375F for about 30 minutes (stirring every 10). Glazed the pecans in honey and cayenne since I don't eat sugar. Tossed the sprouts, pecans, and cheese together with some red wine vinegar. After devouring half the bowl, my guests and I decided the addition of crumbled bacon and chopped dried apricots would be great additions, and we were right. With these changes we will definitely be making this again.

